name: Riata
description: A community bound by legacy. There’s Texas. And then there’s Austin, Texas. Equal parts Lone Star pride, Hill Country roots, and progressive culture. And while the spotlight on Austin grows brighter each day, a big part of its success lies north of downtown in what began as a homestead in the 1830s.  A few modern-day prospectors, led by famed Texan Jerry Jones, staked claim to this beautiful land and began setting a vision in two parts. First, create a destination of culture that recognizes the incredible landscape of Texas Hill Country. Second, build a noteworthy neighborhood that celebrates opportunity, connection, and legacy.That vision is Riata. A community of over 2,000 residences in North Austin, a region where today – as foreseen three decades ago – forward-looking retail, tech innovation, local craft, and incredible neighborly culture are in full bloom.

name: Cortland River Place
description: Located minutes away from Lake Travis and highly rated Leander ISD schools, our community offers everything to love about North Austin living at your front door. Spacious floor plans and upgraded features in select homes will make you proud to call any of our newly renovated one and two-bedroom apartments home.Convenience to River Place Medical and major tech companies like NVIDIA makes your everyday commute a breeze. And when you’re considering your weekend (or weeknight) plans, you have plenty of options nearby. Take a scenic hike along River Place Nature Trail, treat yourself to some retail therapy at The Domain, or drive about 10 minutes to Lake Travis for a lakeside dinner as the sun sets. Make sure to also check out our sister communities nearby: Paseo at Bee Cave, Cortland Bluff Springs, Cortland Onion Creek, and Cortland Arboretum.

Make sure to also check out our sister communities nearby: Paseo at Bee Cave, Cortland Bluff Springs, Cortland Onion Creek, and Cortland Southpark Meadows.

name: The Aspect
description: Located in the desirable East Riverside and Montopolos area, The Aspect is just minutes from downtown Austin. Skyline views and designer features like smoky quartz countertops and Nest Learning thermostats will make you proud to call Aspect your home. Residents enjoy access to our 24/7 gym, resident clubhouse, dog park, sparkling pool, and business center. Our location is easily accessible to HWY 71 and 35, and a draw for the area’s major employers like Oracle, Google and Tesla. When you are considering your weekend plans, you have plenty of options nearby. Spend an afternoon at Lady Bird Lake; then enjoy a variety of entertainment including live music at some Austin’s most famous venues. The Aspect has everything you need to feel at home. We have carports and garages, along with open and free parking.

name: Bell Southpark
description:
Surround yourself in nineteen acres of pristine landscaping, best-in-class amenities, and towering oak trees that give Bell Southpark apartments the feelings of home in South Austin. Bell Southpark offers one, two and three bedroom homes with upscale features and an attention to detail unrivaled across other apartment communities in Austin, TX.

From the natural look of the hardwood-inspired flooring to the clean lines of the frameless shower enclosures, each apartment incorporates designer finishes with you in mind. In your kitchen, the custom cabinetry blends the earth tones of the granite counters and the cool stainless steel finish of the Energy Star-certified Whirlpool appliances.

When you’re not exploring the four-acre park and nature trail, you can unwind beside the indoor and outdoor fireplaces or engage in some friendly competition in the game room. The easy access to Interstate 35 also places you near the area’s top employers, as well as shopping at Southpark Meadows.

name: Fivetwo at Highland
description: Introducing you to Fivetwo at Highland, an appealing Austin community with laid-back luxury. Our artfully designed apartments feature gourmet kitchens, modern finishes, French doors, upscale appliances, and notably high 12-foot ceilings. Our dog-friendly apartments in Downtown Austin give you the best of city living right outside your door with our neighborhood market, coffee house, salon, and yoga studio. When you want to relax, Fivetwo lets you unwind in one of our pool courtyards, complete with a shaded outdoor pool table, fire pit, and lawn games. Four-legged friends also live the luxe life at Fivetwo, with pet-friendly spaces and a choice of two dog runs. Make Fivetwo at Highland yours today.

No matter what you’re looking for in your next home, you’re sure to find it here at 44 South.

name: Presidium Waterford
description:
A 283-unit, Class-A, multifamily development in Austin, TX, Presidium Waterford is just minutes from the Domain (also known as Austin’s second downtown), and the Austin FC professional soccer stadium that kicked off their inaugural season this April.

The area houses numerous Fortune 500 companies and includes copious amounts of office and industrial space, along with a plethora of retail for the convenience and enjoyment of residents.

The newly passed Project Connect program, on track to add a diverse selection of transportation options throughout the Austin MSA, has a light rail dedicated within a ten-minute walk.  Both the Red and Purple lines connect to the airport and downtown.

Additionally, Presidium Waterford is one of the few multifamily sites available along the US-183-corridor, allowing for direct access to either Highway Loop 1 or Interstate 35. This provides tremendous ease of access to all major commercial hubs in and around the City – and is unmatched by any of the surrounding luxury housing options.
